The paper discusses neural architecture search (NAS) algorithms and their performance on multiple datasets, which are common topics in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, since the focus is on NAS algorithms and their performance, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DC.
